<item>
            <title>[LU-3872] rpmlint error - lustre/tests/Makefile.am has lustre/tests/clientapi/simple_test.c as scripts</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3872</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The lustre/tests/Makefile.am has file permission of lustre/tests/clientapi/simple_test.c as scripts (nobase_noinst_SCRIPTS), so it is executable. It should be nobase_noinst_DATA. This caused the rpmlint check to fail when packaging it into a development RPM package: &quot;E: spurious-executable-perm (Badness: 50)&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;A Gerrit submission for review is on its way.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>SLES 11 SP2, CentOS 6.4</environment>
